I have analyzed the feedback and the accompanying screenshots. My course of action is to make several adjustments to the `lamp.tsx` component and the `MissionSection.tsx` component to resolve the visual artifacts and layout issues in the bottom part of the homepage.

1.  **Fix Header Cut-off (Purple Arrow):** In `src/components/global/lamp.tsx`, the content is being pulled up too high, causing the title to be clipped. I will reduce the negative vertical translation on the content wrapper to move it down and give it adequate space.

2.  **Expand Lamp Effect (Yellow Arrows):** To eliminate the hard rectangular edges of the lamp's light effect, I will significantly increase the width and height of the conic gradient elements within `lamp.tsx`. This will make the light feel more expansive and blend more smoothly into the background, covering the same area as the particle effect as requested.

3.  **Remove Bottom Sliver (Red Arrows):** The sliver of background at the bottom is caused by padding inside the `LampContainer` combined with a negative margin on the `MissionSection`. I will remove the bottom padding from `lamp.tsx` and the corresponding negative margin from `MissionSection.tsx`. This will ensure the particle effect extends to the very bottom of the component, flush with the footer.

These changes should create a cleaner, more immersive, and polished final section for the homepage.

