I have analyzed the feedback and the provided screenshots. The remaining issues are all located in the bottom "Mission" section, which is composed of the `MissionSection` and `LampContainer` components. My course of action is to refine the styling within these components to fix the cut-off title, expand the lamp's lighting effect to remove artifacts, and ensure the sparkles extend to the very bottom of the component.

1.  **`src/components/global/lamp.tsx`:** I will make several adjustments here to address all three issues.
    *   **(Cut-off Title):** To give the title more space at the top, I will reduce the negative vertical translation of the content container, moving it down slightly so it is no longer clipped by the elements above it.
    *   **(Lamp Artifacts):** To eliminate the rectangular artifacts from the lamp effect, I will significantly increase the width and height of the `motion.div` elements that generate the conic gradients. This will make the light source much larger and more diffuse, allowing it to blend smoothly into the background instead of creating hard edges.
    *   **(Bottom Sliver):** To remove the sliver of background below the sparkles, I will remove the bottom padding from the main `LampContainer` `div`. This will ensure the container, and the absolutely positioned sparkles within it, extend to the very bottom edge.

2.  **`src/components/home/MissionSection.tsx`:** To complement the change in `lamp.tsx` and create a cleaner layout, I will remove the negative bottom margin from the `<section>` element. This will prevent layout issues where the footer is pulled up imperfectly, which was likely contributing to the sliver of background being visible.

These changes should result in a polished final appearance for the bottom section of the homepage.

