I have analyzed the user's feedback and identified four key areas for improvement. My course of action will address the visual styling of the Mission section, including the lamp effect and title, and resolve technical warnings related to legacy Next.js Image component properties.

1.  **`src/components/global/lamp.tsx`:**
    *   **Expand Lamp Effect:** To ensure the lamp's light cone covers the entire vertical area of the sparkles, I will increase the vertical scaling of the gradient container. I will change the `scale-y-150` class to `scale-y-200`, which will stretch the effect downwards and eliminate the gap at the bottom.
    *   **Reduce Light Intensity:** To address the "light pollution," I will darken the colors that create the lamp effect. I will change the conic gradient's color from `from-neutral-500` to a darker `from-neutral-600`. Additionally, I will adjust the blur effect layers, changing `bg-neutral-500` to `bg-neutral-700` (with opacity reduced to `opacity-40`) and `bg-neutral-400` to `bg-neutral-500` to decrease overall brightness. The horizontal "lamp line" will also be toned down from `bg-neutral-400` to `bg-neutral-500`.

2.  **`src/components/home/MissionSection.tsx`:**
    *   **Apply Title Gradient:** To match the styling of other section headers, I will update the title "THE RISE OF COGNITIVE CAPITALISM." I will replace the existing `bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-300 to-neutral-500` classes with `bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-neutral-600`. I will also change the font weight from `font-medium` to `font-bold` for consistency.

3.  **`src/components/home/HeroSection.tsx`:**
    *   **Update Image Component:** To resolve the legacy prop warnings, I will update the `<Image>` component used for the `pcp.gif`. I will replace the deprecated `layout="fill"` and `objectFit="cover"` props with the modern equivalent: the `fill` boolean prop and the `object-cover` utility class.

4.  **`src/components/home/FeaturesSection.tsx`:**
    *   **Update Image Component:** Similarly, I will update the `<Image>` components for the feature icons. The `layout="fill"` and `objectFit="cover"` props will be replaced with the `fill` prop and the `object-cover` class, aligning them with current Next.js best practices and removing the console warnings.

These changes will resolve all the visual and technical issues identified in the current cycle.

